parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels sticky or binds

making it difficult to turn; the vehicle pulls to one side or the other; the steering wheel requires excessive force to turn; the vehicle is difficult to keep in a straight line; the steering wheel jerks or sticks when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause physical harm, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Airbag deploys suddenly while the vehicle is parked or in motion
without any apparent reason or impact

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system malfunction can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, or unintended deployment, which can cause physical harm or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag light stays on consistently while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag deployment failure can lead to physical harm or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag fails to deploy in the event of an accident
airbag deploys with metal shards or rods
